Due to COVID-19 protocols, the Royal House has decided the remains of the king will not lie in state at the Royal Palace. KWA-NONGOMA - Former President Jacob Zuma and KZN Premier Sihle Zikalala have joined mourners at the Royal House in KwaNongoma on Sunday. They will be paying their respects to the late AmaZulu King Goodwill Zwelithini. Due to COVID-19 protocols, the Royal House has decided the remains of the king will not lie in state at the Royal Palace. READ:Â Remembering King Zwelithini: Drama unfolding at the Royal Family house A memorial service will be held on Thursday and the burial details are still unclear. eNCA senior reporter, Siphamandla Goge spoke to Zuma when he arrived. Watch the video above.